Loosing my mind a bit with this.

Using standard Products objects, Iâ€™m trying to get the `hs_lastmodifieddate` value including the _*time*_ as displayed in the Products section of the CRM.


```{% set products = crm_objects("product", "limit=50&amp;orderBy=-hs_lastmodifieddate", "name,product_slug,price,detail_category,description,hs_sku,hs_lastmodifieddate") %}
{% for product in products.results %}
    &lt;div class="product"&gt;
        &lt;h2&gt;{{ product.name }}&lt;/h2&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;product_slug: {{ product.product_slug }}&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;price: {{ product.price }}&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;detail_category: {{ product.detail_category }}&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;SKU: {{ product.hs_sku }}&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;hs_lastmodifieddate: {{ product.hs_lastmodifieddate }}&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
{% endfor %}```
Then I only get the date;

```product_slug: 2025-volvo
price:
detail_category:
SKU: 696025a
hs_lastmodifieddate: 2/12/25```
